ployee for responsibility  supervision  and support of the community and where expressions of civility are not  superficial behaviors  but manifestations of genuine caring  The Superintendent formed the Equity Committee as a barometer to monitor issues that affect these cultural values  The Equity Committee meets to provide a forum in which to review equity related issues and resolutions to the Superintendent   They review the annual Employee Survey and provide feedback to the Superintendent  Equity Committee Info Equity Home FAQs Submit a Concern Review Posted Issues VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 